<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-21T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/7727</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-21T20:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.08 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8764. My 8748, February 20. <persName corresp="#p_FPv1">Fürstenberg</persName> sent the following message to <persName corresp="#p_CvCCO1">Czernin</persName> yesterday: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>As soon as the text, which has been mutilated in several
                                        places, has been definitely established I shall ask His
                                        Majesty to receive me <pb facs="0221" n="129" xml:id="pg_129"/> in order that I may deliver the
                                        message to him tomorrow evening, February 21.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>The Austro-Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs has sent the
                                following supplementary message to the Ambassador at Madrid: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>If Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName> assents
                                        to the King’s proposal and sends a representative to discuss
                                        matters with me he should send some one who speaks either
                                        French or German as I do not know English well enough to
                                        discuss such weighty matters.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>